      • COL_PROCESSED

        public static final java.lang.String COL_PROCESSED
        A flag indicating whether this message has been handled. for outgoing messages this means sent. for incoming messages this means decrypted and added to the obj table. decrypted messages may stall because they require the user to request a new key from the server. generally speaking the time frame should jump directly to a new one, and everyone should use the same so a thread that wakes up on any new key discovery can probably just rescan all the messages without too much fuss.
        See Also:
